Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @filo pastry sheets{1/2} from the fridge and bring it to room temperature. Remove it from the packet and lay flat on the counter, covered with a damp #tea towel{}.

Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{225%g}. Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Trim the @carrots{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the mushrooms and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Stir in the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{15%g} and @water{125%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once thickened, add the @baby spinach{100%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @truffle zest{1} and cheese until fully combined, then remove from the heat. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Transfer the pie filling to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Halve the filo pastry sheets to make squares. Scrunch each square into a very loose ball and place on top of the filling. Repeat until the whole pie is covered, making sure not to overcrowd the pastry. Drizzle the whole pie with @oil{}.

Once the carrots have roasted for about ~{15%minutes}, move them to the middle shelf and bake the pie on the top shelf until the filo is golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

When everything is ready, serve your filo pie in bowls with the roasted carrots alongside. Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've chosen to add chicken to your meal, before you cook the shallot in the step above, add the diced chicken to the pan and cook until browned on the outside, 3-4 mins. Add the shallot to the chicken and continue with the recipe as instructed. Important: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> Step 4 MOD: Important: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.